                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18130407-133-off703 t18130407-133-crimeloc706"></join>, at one o'clock noon day. All I know, I lost it out of the chaise.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18130407-133-person1188">
                  JOHN 
                  RAY
               <interp inst="t18130407-133-person1188" type="surname" value="RAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18130407-133-person1188" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18130407-133-person1188" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner stand in Dutchess-street; he pulled the coat off the driving-box, and put it in a green bag that he had under his arm. I called out stop thief; a man in Cavendish-street took him in custody.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18130407-133-person1189">
                  THOMAS 
                  READ
               <interp inst="t18130407-133-person1189" type="surname" value="READ"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18130407-133-person1189" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18130407-133-person1189" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard the man cry out stop thief; I ran after the prisoner, stopped him, and secured him. I produce the coat.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. It is my coat.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw the great coat in the street; I put it in my bag, and as I was going along Portland-street the officer stopped me.</p>
